1
00:00:04,270 --> 00:00:11,110
I can't imagine a more timely passage than the one I've been asked to speak on this morning.

2
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:22,290
Because at its heart, it's about looking beyond our present anxiety and seeing God and seeing His purposes,

3
00:00:22,950 --> 00:00:26,130
His unstoppable purposes at work in the world.

4
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:35,340
But before I get too deep into the passage, I want to take a little slice of my own life and share it with you.

5
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:41,210
because it connects, I think, to the way the passage describes the emotions flying around

6
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:49,120
the room. So here's a ritual that repeats nearly every Friday in the Reimer household.

7
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:55,980
Jenny and I wake up, sometimes together, though usually she beats me to it, I have to admit that

8
00:00:55,980 --> 00:01:02,250
frankly, and Ariana is often at this point still sleeping. She's usually in her own bed,

9
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:06,970
but occasionally, like if she's woken up at five with the night frights or something like that,

10
00:01:07,550 --> 00:01:11,570
She's between us at some bizarre acrobatic angle,

11
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:13,210
so her feet are in my face,

12
00:01:13,430 --> 00:01:16,110
and her head is resting on Jenny's stomach,

13
00:01:16,270 --> 00:01:18,770
and she's got a fistful of Jenny's hair,

14
00:01:19,310 --> 00:01:21,490
and she's just spread-eagled.

15
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:24,690
It's amazing the contorting positions she can put herself into.

16
00:01:26,220 --> 00:01:28,360
And about a half an hour after this point,

17
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:31,520
three college students, three tousle-headed college students,

18
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:35,120
show up at my apartment at the glass door to my living room

19
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:41,960
in faded t-shirts and running shoes, and so I groggily drag myself off the couch, out of bed,

20
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:47,880
put on my own running shoes, and it's off we go for about three and a half, four miles of

21
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:54,860
self-inflicted torture. Now at this point, Ariana is usually still snuggled with mommy,

22
00:01:55,360 --> 00:02:00,980
or on the couch, just kind of looking in that sort of dazed, I just woke up frame of mind.

23
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:04,530
So she doesn't care that Daddy is leaving to go jogging.

24
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:06,030
It doesn't really faze her.

25
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:06,870
She's too sleepy.

26
00:02:07,330 --> 00:02:09,270
She's too content to care.

27
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:13,630
On the other hand, when I get back,

28
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:17,240
and the college students go home and go about their Fridays,

29
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,060
and I jump in the shower, and I wolf down breakfast,

30
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:23,200
and I, you know, throw on my clothes and head out the door,

31
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:27,160
Ariana, my two-year-old daughter, is right there beside me,

32
00:02:27,740 --> 00:02:28,960
following me out the door.

33
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:33,860
and here's something that invariably happens.

34
00:02:34,890 --> 00:02:38,350
I shut the door ever so gingerly behind myself

35
00:02:38,350 --> 00:02:40,940
to make sure she doesn't get bonked or hurt

36
00:02:40,940 --> 00:02:46,000
and she just doesn't understand.

37
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:47,840
I mean, why isn't she going with me?

38
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:49,240
She's in her PJ.

39
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,900
She's got her dolly that goes potty.

40
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:52,080
I mean, she's ready to go.

41
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:53,820
Why can't she come?

42
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:56,590
And so the door clicks shut

43
00:02:56,590 --> 00:03:03,430
and I hear this wail on the other side of the door

44
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:04,430
which is, Mama!

45
00:03:05,790 --> 00:03:06,930
Because I'm Mama too.

46
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:08,510
Jenny's mama, I'm mama.

47
00:03:08,890 --> 00:03:10,230
We're both mama at this point.

48
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,900
And I hear this wailing through the door,

49
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:19,960
and I hear this wailing as I walk down the hallway,

50
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,580
out of my apartment complex,

51
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,460
mixed with the sounds of Jenny trying to distract her and soothe her.

52
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:30,320
And I hear this wailing in my head as I climb into the truck

53
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:34,410
to go to school or to work or to wherever it is I'm going that Friday.

54
00:03:39,790 --> 00:03:41,550
And, yeah, I've gotten used to this.

55
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:44,230
It's something all of us parents go through.

56
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:50,030
But the sound that I hear in my head is the sound of a two-year-old

57
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:54,380
that just doesn't understand why I'm leaving.

58
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:58,080
She doesn't care about the higher purposes behind my day

59
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:02,420
or why I go to work or why I study or why I go through this daily grind.

60
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:09,830
All she sees is me leaving, and all she wants to do is come with me.

61
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:10,890
That's it.

62
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:19,400
And see, that is something like the mood that surrounds Jesus

63
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:23,700
in the room where he and his disciples have just eaten their last meal,

64
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:27,960
the last one they'll eat prior to Jesus' crucifixion.

65
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:34,780
They were worried, and let's be honest, they had good cause to be worried,

66
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:41,830
because in chapter 13, Judas Iscariot, the disciple who eventually betrays Jesus,

67
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:45,550
has already left the meal in a big hurry with no explanation,

68
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:49,750
you know, just a few nervous glances from side to side, and he's gone.

69
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:53,750
He's out the door without a word, and they're beginning to talk.

70
00:04:53,990 --> 00:04:55,050
What was that all about?

71
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:04,230
And to make matters worse than Judas' awkward exit,

72
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:10,530
Jesus is also hinting in subtle and maybe not so subtle ways that he's going to leave too.

73
00:05:10,530 --> 00:05:13,020
He says,

74
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:17,000
My children, I will be with you only a little longer.

75
00:05:18,570 --> 00:05:20,950
You will look for me just as I told the Jews,

76
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:24,790
so I tell you now where I am going.

77
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,430
You can't come.

78
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:34,290
to which the outspoken leader of the disciples, Peter, responds,

79
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:38,450
Lord, why can't I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you.

80
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:44,160
And what Jesus says next just makes matters worse.

81
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:47,720
I'm imagining the temperature in the room dropped about 30 degrees

82
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:50,600
when Jesus said this next sentence.

83
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:54,810
Huh, will you really lay down your life for me?

84
00:05:56,080 --> 00:06:02,900
I tell you the truth, before the rooster crows, you will disown me three times.

85
00:06:03,180 --> 00:06:10,870
And the door swings shut, and the two-year-old starts to cry.

86
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:22,200
But see, then, like Jenny, picking up Ariana just to soothe her and comfort her and distract her,

87
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:28,430
Jesus turns to all of his disciples in their fear and in their confusion,

88
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:34,080
some probably with tears streaming down their face at this point,

89
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,900
and he speaks gently to them.

90
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:37,900
He comforts them.

91
00:06:38,340 --> 00:06:41,330
He explains matters to them.

92
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:48,220
And here is our very long, very meaty passage this morning.

93
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:51,600
John, chapter 14, in its entirety.

94
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,360
Do not let your hearts be troubled.

95
00:06:59,130 --> 00:06:59,870
Trust in God.

96
00:07:00,610 --> 00:07:01,630
Trust also in me.

97
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:06,060
In my Father's house are many rooms.

98
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:09,310
If it were not so, I would have told you.

99
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:13,290
I am going to prepare a place for you.

100
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:16,290
I will come back and take you to be with me,

101
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:20,470
that you also may be where I am.

102
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:26,370
You know the way to the place I'm going.

103
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:29,930
Thomas said to him,

104
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:34,100
Lord, we don't know where you're going,

105
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,620
so how can we know the way?

106
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,950
Maybe he said it in a more high-pitched voice

107
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,850
than the one I just read it in.

108
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,420
Jesus answered, I am the way,

109
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:50,180
and the truth, and the life.

110
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:54,140
no one comes to the Father except through me.

111
00:07:55,330 --> 00:07:59,270
If you really knew me, you would know my Father as well.

112
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:03,860
From now on, you do know him and have seen him.

113
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:09,060
Philip said, Lord, show us the Father

114
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:14,750
and that'll be enough. Jesus answered, don't you

115
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:19,740
know me, Philip? Even after I have been among you such a

116
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:23,680
long time, anyone who has seen me has seen the Father.

117
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:26,400
How can you say, show us the Father?

118
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:31,260
Don't you believe that I am in the Father and that the Father is in me?

119
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,560
The words I say are not just my own.

120
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:39,520
Rather, it is the Father living in me who is doing the work.

121
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:46,410
Believe me when I say to you that I am in the Father and the Father is in me.

122
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:52,110
Or at least believe the miracles, the evidence of the miracles themselves.

123
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,280
I tell you the truth.

124
00:08:55,280 --> 00:09:01,280
Anyone who has faith in me, anyone, will do what I have been doing.

125
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:07,620
He will do even greater things than these, because I am going to the Father.

126
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:14,800
And I will do whatever you ask in my name, so that the Son may bring glory to the Father.

127
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:20,280
You may ask for anything in my name, and I will do it.

128
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:26,240
If you love me, you will obey what I command.

129
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:35,890
I will ask the Father, and He will give you another Counselor to be with you forever, the Spirit of Truth.

130
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:42,100
The world cannot accept Him, because it neither sees Him nor knows Him.

131
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:48,610
But you know Him, for He lives with you and will be in you.

132
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:57,640
I will not leave you as orphans. I will come to you.

133
00:09:57,640 --> 00:10:04,570
Before long, the world will not see me anymore, but you will see me.

134
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:07,910
Because I live, you also will live.

135
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:20,240
On that day, you will realize that I am in my Father, and you are in me, and I am in you.

136
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:27,540
Whoever has my commands and obeys them, he is the one who loves me.

137
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:37,270
He who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I too will love him and show myself to him.

138
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:42,980
Then Judas, not Judas Iscariot, said,

139
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:51,370
But Lord, why do you intend to show yourself to us and not the world?

140
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:53,690
I mean, come on, Jesus, let's go public with this.

141
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:56,840
And Jesus replied,

142
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:02,940
If anyone loves me, he will obey my teaching.

143
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:10,340
My Father will love him, and we will come to him and make our home with him.

144
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:15,660
He who does not love me will not obey my teaching.

145
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:19,660
These words you hear are not my own.

146
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,440
They belong to the Father who sent me.

147
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:28,320
All that I have spoken while still with you, all this I have spoken while still with you.

148
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:39,450
But the Counselor, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, will teach you all things and remind you of everything I have said to you.

149
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:44,090
Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you.

150
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:46,750
I do not give to you as the world gives.

151
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:52,380
Do not let your hearts be troubled, and do not be afraid.

152
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,580
That's the refrain.

153
00:11:57,510 --> 00:12:01,670
You heard me say, I'm going away, and I'm coming back to you.

154
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:05,930
If you loved me, you would be glad that I am going to the Father,

155
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:08,130
for the Father is greater than I.

156
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:15,390
I have told you now before it happens, so that when it does happen, you will believe.

157
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:21,760
I will not speak with you much longer, for the Prince of this world is coming.

158
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:27,190
He has no hold on me, but the world must learn that I love the Father

159
00:12:27,190 --> 00:12:31,390
and that I do exactly what my Father has commanded me.

160
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,560
There's a lot here to unpack.

161
00:12:45,460 --> 00:12:48,900
For one, Jesus is preparing his followers, most obviously,

162
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,160
for the shock of his crucifixion,

163
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:55,510
the time that's soon coming when all the miracles,

164
00:12:55,770 --> 00:12:57,690
all the exorcisms, all the healings,

165
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,830
all the wisdom that Jesus taught

166
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:02,530
is just going to be seemingly swallowed up

167
00:13:02,530 --> 00:13:06,010
by this evil, catastrophic tragedy.

168
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,720
As Jesus puts it, the prince of this world is coming,

169
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:17,840
and he, meaning Satan, has no hold on me.

170
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:21,120
But the world must learn that I love the Father

171
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:24,140
and that I do exactly what my Father has commanded me.

172
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:28,000
In other words, the world needs to see that I, Jesus,

173
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:33,700
obey my Father to the bitter end, even crucifixion.

174
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:38,740
But more important than bracing his disciples for the worst,

175
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:47,610
beyond the crucifixion is something deeper something that even death on a cross will not

176
00:13:47,610 --> 00:13:57,200
and cannot destroy his disciples have an unbroken and unbreakable connection to him

177
00:13:57,200 --> 00:14:07,160
and an unbroken and unbreakable connection to god the father through him you see thomas

178
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:13,380
echoes peter he pleads with jesus and this is my paraphrase so bear with me what's all this

179
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:19,230
talk about you leaving? Leaving where? How are we supposed to find our way back to you when we don't

180
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:32,170
even know your destination? And Jesus replies, I'm the way, I'm the destination, and the truth,

181
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:40,400
and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me. If you really knew me, you would know

182
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:47,380
my Father as well. From now on, you do know him and have seen him. And another disciple, Philip,

183
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:56,300
still not quite getting it, says. Look, Jesus, come on, enough with the riddles already.

184
00:14:57,330 --> 00:15:04,030
Just show us God. Just make him show up right here, right now, in this room, in the flesh,

185
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:16,230
please. Just remove all of our doubts. You tell us to trust the Father, your Father, to trust this

186
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:25,400
God. So show us God already. Don't beat around the bush. Don't tell us you're leaving to go back to

187
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:33,000
the Father. Just show us your Father. Bring him here. Make him our Father, and that'll be enough

188
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:44,330
no matter what happens to us or to you. Just show us the Father, please, Jesus. And so then Jesus

189
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:53,650
drops the bomb. He made a claim here that is so outrageous that the world has either been owning

190
00:15:53,650 --> 00:16:01,300
it, ignoring it, or just going to great lengths to reject it ever since. He says, don't you know

191
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:10,810
me, Philip? Even after I have been among you such a long time, anyone who has seen me has seen the

192
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:17,440
Father. How can you say, show us the Father? Don't you believe that I am in the Father and that the

193
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:26,200
Father is in me? The words I say to you are not just my own. Rather, it is the Father living in me

194
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:33,800
who is doing the work. Believe me when I say to you, Philip, that I am in the Father and that the

195
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:40,810
Father is in me. Or at least believe in the evidence of the miracles themselves. I tell you

196
00:16:40,810 --> 00:16:47,680
the truth, anyone who has faith in me will do what I have been doing. Anyone. He will do even greater

197
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:54,760
things than these because I am going to the Father. And I will do whatever you ask in my name

198
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:58,790
so that the Son may bring glory to the Father.

199
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:02,430
You may ask for anything in my name, and I will do it.

200
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,480
You've seen God.

201
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:07,590
You've seen me.

202
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:11,970
You're looking at him.

203
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,920
You've seen all of the Father that you need to see.

204
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:22,380
Everything I've said and done, those were his words and his doing.

205
00:17:23,590 --> 00:17:24,110
Believe it.

206
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:27,750
You say the Father is enough for you, and I absolutely agree with you, Philip,

207
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:31,460
because you've seen me and believed in me.

208
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:40,060
you, Philip, you, disciples, will begin to do the things that you've seen me doing. You will begin

209
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:50,430
to speak the things that you've heard me teaching. You've listened to the Father. I've listened to

210
00:17:50,430 --> 00:18:01,250
the Father. You will do all the things that I've been doing, and you will do more. In fact, let's

211
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:07,630
just do the math, disciples. There won't just be one of me anymore. There will be armies of me,

212
00:18:07,630 --> 00:18:17,200
followers of me, attuned to God's will, attuned to the Father's will, as I have been attuned

213
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:32,200
to the Father's will. And they, you, will do his work in the world. You see, Jesus is trying to

214
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:39,920
teach a very simple, very profound thing in this time of great anxiety. As Henry Blackaby puts it,

215
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:45,240
he's saying, hey, disciples, join God in what he's already doing.

216
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,880
And he's not simply telling them what to do.

217
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:52,700
He's giving them the power to do it.

218
00:18:54,990 --> 00:18:57,550
If you love me, you will obey what I command.

219
00:18:59,130 --> 00:19:03,630
And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another counselor

220
00:19:03,630 --> 00:19:08,960
to be with you forever, the Spirit of truth.

221
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:14,200
The world cannot accept him because it neither sees him nor knows him.

222
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:25,970
but you know him for he lives with you and will be in you. I will not leave you as orphans. I will

223
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:35,060
come to you. I will come to you. Before long the world will not see me anymore but you will see me

224
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:42,680
because I live you also will live. Jesus promises that he will not leave his disciples, that he will

